main event: Sighting of three bright, round, luminous objects in the sky near Kingsville, Maryland on February 25, 1953.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be self-illuminated and about 40 degrees above the horizon.
One of the objects appeared to dim and brighten alternately at intervals of about one second.
The objects were first observed in the clear sky, between the clouds, and the last time they were observed was behind the clouds.
The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes.
The observer, Captain from the Army Chemical Center, had 20/20 vision corrected by eyeglasses and a Bachelor's degree in Physics.
witnesses: Captain from the Army Chemical Center
